results.lead_paragraph: WITH the two greatest nations on earth now committed to the race for the moon, there can be no doubt that we will see lunar landings in the Nineteen Seventies (or even the Sixties) and expeditions to the planets a little later. Such matters as the colonization of the moon and planets are therefore no longer the concern of fantasy; indeed, it is now unrealistic and escapist not to examine them seriously.

results.snippet: CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla., Nov. 25 (AP) -- The United States will try again next week to rocket a chimpanzee three times around the earth in the last planned launching before a United States astronaut is placed in orbit.

headline.main: Weird World of Weightlessness; Strange and even ominous things happen when man is not held down by gravity, as one who has had the experience can testify. World of Weightlessness

results.snippet: RUSSIA'S Gherman Titov, traveling in a state of weightlessness during most of his twenty-five-hour orbit around the earth, experienced numerous sensations as a result of that condition. Some of them were "unpleasant feelings, resembling seasickness."
